        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          I didn't like the tactics after we went 2-1 up. I can understand starting conservatively, sitting back allowing PSG possession and waiting for mistakes because a 0-0 draw suited us. Once we scored the 2nd though, a draw was no good. The period from going a goal down to a goal up was excellent. We had the majority of that ball- overtook their match total possession stats, had them penned in and it looked more likely we'd get a 3rd than they would score a 2nd. Then.... we sat back again. I think we gave them far too much respect. Their big chances came largely when we were inviting pressure (and chasing the game at 2-2 of course, when the match descended into kitchen sink football). The performance was akin to a 2nd leg of a knockout tie where any draw would see us through. Not a good mind-set. As it is, with Real and Bayern likely finishing 2nd, it wasn't paramount we topped the group. Whoever we get will be prove a tough opponent.
